desc.en: <@gd.key>Item Control Ports</> limit the type and quantity of items allowed to pass through transport belts. Use <@gd.key>Item Control Ports</> in blueprints to mark the type of items to be moved onto various transport belt sections.
The <@gd.key>Belt Bridge</> allows a transport belt to go over another without disrupting the flow of items on both belts.
The <@gd.key>Converger</> can converge product flows of 3 transport belts into a single belt.

<@gd.key>Pipe Control Ports</> can limit the fluid and the quantity of fluids allowed to pass through pipelines. Use <@gd.key>Pipe Control Ports</> in blueprints to mark the type of fluid to be moved through various pipelines.
The <@gd.key>Pipe Bridge</> allows a pipeline to go over another without disrupting the flow of fluids in both pipelines.
The <@gd.key>Pipe Converger</> can converge up to 3 pipelines into a single pipeline.
<@gd.key>Pipe Splitters</> can <@gd.key>split 1 pipeline into 2 or 3 pipelines</> to divide fluid flow.
The <@gd.key>Splitter</> can split the product flow of 1 transport belt to up to 3 transport belts.

<@gd.key>Easy Stashes</> provides direct access to the local <@gd.key>Depot</>. They are convenient for those who need to acquire or store items in the <@gd.key>Depot</> when traveling in the wilderness.

Fluid Supply Units can only be placed near a lake or other water bodies. When placed, its fluid outlet must be <@gd.key>above the water body</>. Once <@gd.key>connected to the power grid</>, the Fluid Supply Unit can supply fluids into the target area.
A Fluid Tank can store <@gd.key>a single type of fluid</> delivered to it via pipelines.
Items moved into the <@gd.key>Depot Loader</> via transport belts will be stored in the Depot.

The <@gd.key>Depot Bus Section</> must be connected to a <@gd.key>Depot Bus Port</> or other active Depot Bus Sections. Once active, Depot Loaders and Depot Unloaders can be attached to the Depot Bus.

The <@gd.key>Depot Bus Port</> can be placed in the Core AIC Area, while the <@gd.key>Depot Bus Section</> must be connected to a <@gd.key>Depot Bus Port</> or other active Depot Bus Sections. Depot Loaders and Depot Unloaders can be attached to an active Depot Bus.
<@gd.key>Memo Beacons</> may include icons and messages that other explorers wish to convey about the location.

Place <@gd.key>Electric Pylons</> in the Core AIC Area of the <@gd.key>PAC</> to automatically connect them to the grid. Connected Electric Pylons can supply power to facilities within their power supply radius.

The Xiranite Pylon is a special facility of Wuling. Like an improved Electric Pylon, it can supply power to nearby facilities and provide short-range power transmission. The Xiranite Pylon <@gd.key>automatically connects</> to the Protocol Automation-Core (PAC) and any <@gd.key>Xiranite Relays</> outside the Core AIC Area within an 80-meter radius, and to other <@gd.key>Xiranite Pylons</> and power facilities outside the Core AIC Area within a 30-meter radius.

The <@gd.key>Relay Tower</> is a key power transmission facility. Relay Towers can be used to transmit power to other Relay Towers, Electric Pylons, and Electric Nexuses to connect them to the power grid.

The Xiranite Relay is a special facility of Wuling. Like an improved Relay Tower, it can supply power to nearby facilities and provide power transmission. The Xiranite Relay <@gd.key>automatically connects</> to the Protocol Automation-Core (PAC) and any <@gd.key>Xiranite power facilities</> outside the Core AIC Area within an 80-meter radius.

Connect the <@gd.key>Sprinkler</> to a source of water to sprinkle water on the target.
The <@gd.key>Protocol Stash</> can store items. When powered, the Protocol Stash can also deliver stored items to the Depot on a regular basis.
Set up zipline routes with <@gd.key>Zipline Pylons</> to quickly zip from one Pylon to another. Other Zipline Pylons can be selected as destinations to quickly zip to it.

The <@gd.key>Zipline Tower</> is an improved version of the Zipline Pylon. It has a longer zipline range and allows the creation of zipline routes that pass through multiple <@gd.key>Zipline Towers</> in a single trip.
Use the <@gd.key>Depot Unloader</> to automatically unload items from the Depot onto the connected transport belt.
